result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler J. SHALLOW was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information charging misdemeanor bail jumping, contrary to Section 946.49(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.   No contest plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.   Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for sixty (60) days, under the Huber Law, to commence on 02-11-16 by 6:00 p.m.  Defendant is given 1 day credit.   
$443.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 05-21-16 or 7 days jail.   
Defendant must submit DNA sample.   $100.00 cash bail applied.   
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Minutes.

Settlement Conference Summary.
Plea hearing is set for 01-15-16 at 3:30 p.m.
State's Motion and Demand for Discovery.

Court withdraws the warrant authorized yesterday.
Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 2 for trial.
ARRAIGNMENT - 
Information filed.  Copy served on defense counsel.
Not guilty plea entered.  Jury calendar.
Settlement conference with District Attorney is set for 01-07-16 at 2:30 p.m.
Minutes
Waiver of Right to Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant failed to appear for a preliminary hearing.
State requests warrant.
Court authorizes warrant but will withold issuance of the warrant until 5:00 p.m. on 11-19-15.
Preliminary hearing is reset to 11-19-15 at 3:30 p.m.  If defendant does not show up, the warrant will be issued.
Minutes.
Brian Van Ells, through public defender.

Defendant demands a preliminary hearing.   Preliminary hearing is set for 11-18-15 at 1:30 p.m.   
Minutes.
Notice to Party Furnishing Cash Bail.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of bail jumping.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 11-09-15 at 2:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $100.00 cash with the condition that he maintain absolute sobriety.  Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
